    <item>
      <title>New Year&amp;#039;s Letters - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/01/02/new-years-letters/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/01/02/new-years-letters/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 03 Jan 2025 03:17:36 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7868" class="post-7868 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;New Year&amp;#8217;s Letters&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Yesterday was New Year&amp;#8217;s Day, and I had a bunch of new letters in my mailbox. Many of them were New Year&amp;#8217;s greetings, including one from Mom, who sent me 10,000 bells. Nice! And the letter from Truffles was particularly amusing; she said she resolved to become a sewer worker in 2025!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/truffles-sewer-150x112.jpg" alt="We did it, Jeff, Happy New Year! I resolve to be a sewer worker! No, I'm TOTALLY kidding! That would be SWEATY! 1/1/2025! -Truffles" class="wp-image-7870" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But there was also this one from Whitney, who said she &lt;em&gt;guesses &lt;/em&gt;she&amp;#8217;ll spend some time with me this year, but only because her boyfriend is busy. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/whitney-boyfriend-150x112.jpg" alt="I'm so sure, Jeff, Happy New Year! I guess I'll spend time with you, since my boyfriend is all busy. Sigh...love is hard! 2025? Wow! -Whitney" class="wp-image-7871" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I visited Drift, and he demanded that I hurry up and give him a New Year&amp;#8217;s gift! That&amp;#8217;s not how it works, froggy.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/drift-gift-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: Yo, J-puff! Hurry up and give me a dang New Year's gift!" class="wp-image-7872" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;No gift for Drift, sorry.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He also told me his new year&amp;#8217;s resolution was to get his body fat down to 0.02%! Yeah, I don&amp;#8217;t think that&amp;#8217;s possible (or healthy).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/drift-body-fat-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: This year I'm gonna carve down to 0.02% body fat, rrrrribbit!" class="wp-image-7873" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tortimer was over near town hall, and he said he prepared a New Year&amp;#8217;s fortune for me!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tort-fortune2025-150x112.jpg" alt="Tortimer: Happy New Year, Jeff! I prepared a New Year's fortune for you!" class="wp-image-7874" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The fortune said I&amp;#8217;d have a &amp;#8220;kinda lucky&amp;#8221; year. I&amp;#8217;ll believe it when I see it. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/fortune2025-150x112.jpg" alt="Your fortune: Kinda Lucky. Dreams: Most likely, yes. Love: It should work. Health: No ill signs. Luck favors the foolish." class="wp-image-7875" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline offered me a free racer shirt, and I gladly accepted. It&amp;#8217;ll go with my helmet!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/caroline-racer-150x112.jpg" alt="Caroline: Hey, bunny, you want a racer shirt? 'Cuz I've got a spare." class="wp-image-7876" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I &lt;em&gt;raced &lt;/em&gt;to put the shirt on, and I later stuffed my sandwich shirt into storage at my house.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Drift told me he was so pumped that he was going to practice figure skating until he&amp;#8217;s sick. He then told me that he was on a quest&amp;#8230;for a cockroach.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/drift-cockroach-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: My quest has brought me here at last. My quest...for a cockroach." class="wp-image-7878" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He then said he was so far from home, and he hoped he wasn&amp;#8217;t lost. But this was only a few feet from his house, just a 5-second walk or so. 😛 Filbert might be the weirdest dude in town, but Drift can be pretty odd himself. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tank wanted a new catchphrase to replace &amp;#8220;yip yip,&amp;#8221; so I told him to say &amp;#8220;in 2025&amp;#8221; instead. He actually used it in a fairly appropriate way (with confetti), although this definitely isn&amp;#8217;t going to be one of my funnier phrases.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tank-2025-150x112.jpg" alt="Tank: I'm gonna start throwing that thing around like confetti, in 2025!" class="wp-image-7879" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you haven&amp;#8217;t yet seen my video taking a look back at my 2024 in Animal Crossing (spanning all five core/worldwide AC games), check it out!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="My 2024 in Animal Crossing" width="840" height="473" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BAKA-E9zWtw?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll be back with another entry next week. Happy New Year!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/01/02/new-years-letters/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-01-02T22:17:36-05:00"&gt;January 2, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-01-02T22:19:41-05:00"&gt;January 2, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/truffles-sewer.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>New Year&amp;#039;s Shirt 2025 - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/01/01/new-years-shirt-2025/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/01/01/new-years-shirt-2025/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 23:29:42 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13186" class="post-13186 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;New Year&amp;#8217;s Shirt 2025&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Last night was New Year&amp;#8217;s Eve, and I started up the game about 15 minutes before midnight. Mayor Tortimer was standing outside of town hall, and he stated the obvious.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/RUU_8116-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Tortimer: In case you've been living under a rock, the big countdown is tonight!" class="wp-image-13187" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I stayed for the countdown to 2025&amp;#8230; Happy New Year! 🎉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/accf-newyear2025-sm-150x84.jpg" alt="Happy New Year! I hope this is the best year ever for all of you!" class="wp-image-13188" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The fireworks began, and I made my rounds. I found a new house in the southwest part of town, and Felicity was inside!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/RUU_8117-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Felicity: Well, I'm Felicity, and I'm the newest resident of your awesome town!" class="wp-image-13189" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Since it was after midnight, it was technically 2025 when I met her. For a moment, I was trying to think if she should count as a December or a January arrival. Even after midnight, Animal Crossing games still count a day to be the previous day until the new day &lt;em&gt;officially &lt;/em&gt;starts at 6 a.m. But then I realized that it was a moot point, because clearly her house was there when I loaded up the game on December 31st regardless, even if I didn&amp;#8217;t see it until after midnight. 😛 So she is a December 2024 arrival, but just barely.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She has lived here before, but it&amp;#8217;s been a while; it was back in &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2013/06/08/new-cat-in-town/"&gt;2013&lt;/a&gt;. I don&amp;#8217;t think I was a big fan of hers back then&amp;#8230;will this time be different? I&amp;#8217;m not so sure, but we&amp;#8217;ll see.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I played again this afternoon, and I received several letters in the mail wishing me a happy new year. They were from Ruby, Antonio, Roscoe, Nana, Mint, Mom, and Big Top.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/RUU_8118-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Jeff, It's finally the year 2025! Sweeeet! Is this the year we finally get hoverbikes and jetpacks?! I sure hope so! -Your buddy, Big Top" class="wp-image-13190" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mom also attached 1,000 bells to her letter.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But the main reason I played today is to get the limited-edition New Year&amp;#8217;s shirt for 2025! Tortimer handed it to me outside of town hall.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/RUU_8119-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Tortimer: It's a New Year's shirt. And it's this year's limited-edition model!" class="wp-image-13191" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It has a snake on it, because 2025 is the Year of the Snake in the Chinese zodiac. Here&amp;#8217;s a look at the front and back:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="640" height="390" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/accf-2025shirt-sm-150x91.jpg" alt="The New Year's shirt for 2025 in Animal Crossing: City Folk (ACCF) for Nintendo Wii." class="wp-image-13192" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Don&amp;#8217;t forget to pick yours up, if you&amp;#8217;re interested! I used my Scott character to pick up an extra one too, just in case I accidentally sell this one or something. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Felicity was out and about today, and she is planning on being even more energetic and hyperactive in the new year. Uh-oh, I have a feeling she&amp;#8217;s going to annoy me. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/RUU_8122-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Felicity: This year, I resolve to be even MORE energetic! Yaaaaay, hyperactivity, mimimi!" class="wp-image-13193" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Happy New Year, everyone! I hope 2025 is a good year for us all! Maybe a new game this year? We can only hope!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/01/01/new-years-shirt-2025/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-01-01T18:29:42-05:00"&gt;January 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/RUU_8116-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Zodiac Collection Complete - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/01/01/zodiac-collection-complete/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/01/01/zodiac-collection-complete/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 18:55:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18094" class="post-18094 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Zodiac Collection Complete&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;When I played after Christmas, I received Jingle&amp;#8217;s pic in the mail. It was my reward for correctly delivering all the presents on Toy Day.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I decided to install a new public works project (PWP) before the year ended, and I ultimately chose an illuminated arch. I put it near the train station, just north of my fountain. I paid it off, and it officially opened on Monday, December 30th.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20241230_HNI_0027-250x150.jpg" alt="Isabelle: Welcome to the grand completion ceremony for Forest's vital illuminated arch project!" class="wp-image-18095" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here&amp;#8217;s a look at it once it was all lit up for nighttime:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20241231_HNI_0042-250x150.jpg" alt="My new illuminated arch." class="wp-image-18096" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And here&amp;#8217;s how that whole area looks, including my fountain, metal bench, and illuminated tree:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20241231_HNI_0039-250x150.jpg" alt="My park area in the north part of town." class="wp-image-18097" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It looks really pretty! It was just making me a bit sad that most likely, no visitors will ever see it in person. But I&amp;#8217;ll still enjoy it, and hopefully you&amp;#8217;ll all enjoy the pictures of it here.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Last night was New Year&amp;#8217;s Eve, and I showed up close to midnight. Isabelle was worried that I was going to miss the countdown. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20241231_HNI_0043-250x150.jpg" alt="Isabelle: Oh, Mayor Jeff! You came for the event! I was getting worried because it's already so late!" class="wp-image-18098" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Redd and Rolf were also there, and Isabelle gave me some sparkling cider.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20241231_HNI_0046-250x150.jpg" alt="Isabelle, Jeff, Rolf, and Redd on New Year's Eve." class="wp-image-18099" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At midnight, 2025 began. Happy New Year, everyone! 🥳&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0050-250x150.jpg" alt="Happy New Year! I hope this year is filled with fun and friendship for you all!" class="wp-image-18100" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Of course, I took a few moments to enjoy the fireworks&amp;#8230;especially the 2025 ones.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0052-250x150.jpg" alt="The 2025 fireworks in Animal Crossing: New Leaf." class="wp-image-18101" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0054-250x150.jpg" alt="Enjoying the 2025 fireworks in ACNL." class="wp-image-18102" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I played again this afternoon, and my villagers wished me a happy new year, of course. Some also talked about their plans for 2025.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0057-250x150.jpg" alt="Boots, This year, I'll polish my guns until I can lift you up with one arm!" class="wp-image-18103" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Lolly asked me to dig up her time capsule, so I gladly helped out. She found her school jacket, and that was my reward for helping with the time capsule.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0061-250x150.jpg" alt="Lolly: Oh, right! Let me thank you with a gift. Please accept my school jacket!" class="wp-image-18104" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But she also told me that she was planning on moving away on January 3rd! I talked her out of it, of course, but that was a really close call! If I hadn&amp;#8217;t played today (or tomorrow), she would&amp;#8217;ve been gone! Even though it&amp;#8217;s been years since I&amp;#8217;ve lost someone accidentally, it still is a very real possibility and it&amp;#8217;s bound to happen at some point.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At the plaza, Isabelle was handing out the New Year&amp;#8217;s item. She was talking about how snakes have such a hard life. (2025 is the Year of the Snake in the Chinese zodiac.)&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0065-250x150.jpg" alt="Isabelle: I mean, they have to slither wherever they go! That must be really hard!" class="wp-image-18105" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then gave me the zodiac snake for 2025. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0068-250x150.jpg" alt="The zodiac snake for 2025 in Animal Crossing: New Leaf." class="wp-image-18106" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Seeing as this is the 12th New Year&amp;#8217;s Day since the game&amp;#8217;s US/Europe release, this now completes the collection of zodiac animals! I put them all on display in the left room of my house.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20250101_HNI_0069-250x150.jpg" alt="The 12 zodiac animals." class="wp-image-18107" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you had the Japanese version of the game (or, you know, time traveled), you may have already completed the collection. But it&amp;#8217;s pretty cool to have all of them now. And perhaps playing on New Year&amp;#8217;s Day won&amp;#8217;t be so urgent for me in the future, since the gifts will just repeat going forward. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Happy New Year, everyone! 🎉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/01/01/zodiac-collection-complete/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-01-01T13:55:40-05:00"&gt;January 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-01-01T14:10:25-05:00"&gt;January 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/20241230_HNI_0027.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
