    <item>
      <title>Toy Day, Zodiac Snake - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/28/toy-day-zodiac-snake/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/28/toy-day-zodiac-snake/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Dec 2024 04:23:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8517" class="post-8517 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Toy Day, Zodiac Snake&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;First, just a quick heads-up that the zodiac snake figurine is now available in the &amp;#8220;Special Goods&amp;#8221; section of Nook Shopping. It can be ordered through January 5th, for just 1,600 bells. I ordered a few of them.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="442" height="295" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/zodiac-snake-sm-225x150.jpg" alt="The zodiac snake figurine from Nook Shopping." class="wp-image-8518" sizes="(max-width: 442px) 100vw, 442px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Monday, I went out to Lottie&amp;#8217;s Island to visit the hospital. But when I saw the beautiful sunset there, I had to stop for a few moments and just enjoy its beauty. 😍&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sunset-lottie-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="A beautiful sunset on Lottie's island." class="wp-image-8519" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tuesday was Toy Day (Christmas Eve), so I made sure to find Jingle near the plaza. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/jingle2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Jingle: Ho HO!" class="wp-image-8520" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I helped him out by crafting some wrapping paper, and he rewarded me with some Toy Day stockings. I hung them up in my house, and continued working on Jingle&amp;#8217;s next request of delivering gifts to all of my villagers.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/static-laundry-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Static: Whaddays got in the bag, kiddo? You find some of Santa's old laundry? Heh, you like that one? Gahaha!" class="wp-image-8521" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Yeah, and it&amp;#8217;s got some &lt;em&gt;static &lt;/em&gt;cling! You know anything about that?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A few of my villagers gave me gifts in return, but most did not. I successfully delivered gifts to all of my villagers.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ankha-dashing-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Ankha: Oh! Was Santa indisposed, and you heroically swooped in to deliver presents in his stead? How dashing!" class="wp-image-8522" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, I made a mistake that I didn&amp;#8217;t even realize until tonight as I&amp;#8217;m writing this entry: I didn&amp;#8217;t return to Jingle to get my reward (a Toy Day sleigh)! Oops! I forgot to &lt;em&gt;wrap up&lt;/em&gt; the task, and I bet Jingle was &lt;em&gt;snow&lt;/em&gt; disappointed in me!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Of course, I&amp;#8217;ve completed the task before, and I have my four previous sleighs in storage already, so it&amp;#8217;s not a huge deal. But still, I goofed. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Oddly enough, I did remember something less obvious: I checked the stockings on Wednesday (Christmas Day) to find my photo of Jingle.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/jingle-photo2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Jingle's photo was inside! How sneaky of Santa..." class="wp-image-8523" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Louie asked me to play a treasure hunt game, and I found the treasure in just over a minute. Louie seemed shocked, and he gave me my prize: a shop uniform shirt.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/louie-treasure-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Louie: You found it?" class="wp-image-8524" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Huck the frog was camping over at the campsite. I was not interested in keeping him, so I sent him hopping on his way.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/huck-camper2-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Huck, at the campsite: Heya! Are you from around here? I'm kinda on vacation, just relaxing and focus-grouping a few things..." class="wp-image-8525" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Agent S told me that sometimes she likes to take a deep breath and admire her garbage pail. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/agents-garbage2-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Agent S: Sometimes I just stop what I'm doing, take a breath, and admire my garbage pail." class="wp-image-8526" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, my savings balance reached 105 million bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Thursday, I made my 2nd perfect snowboy of the season. He sent me some ice flooring yesterday.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Agent S was sick with a cold yesterday, so I crafted her some medicine. She gave me a tee and towel in return.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I sold 26 bugs to Flick for a total of 123,750 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Fusion&amp;#8221; for me and Static.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Have a happy New Year! &lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/28/toy-day-zodiac-snake/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-12-28T23:23:15-05:00"&gt;December 28, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-12-28T23:30:37-05:00"&gt;December 28, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/zodiac-snake-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Whale of a Tale - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/28/whale-of-a-tale/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/28/whale-of-a-tale/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Dec 2024 02:22:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7853" class="post-7853 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Whale of a Tale&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Thursday, I shot down Gulliver&amp;#8217;s UFO. It was my 40th UFO shot down in Wild World!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ufo40-150x112.jpg" alt="An unidentified object has crashed in our town!" class="wp-image-7854" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I spoke with Filbert, he told me that my face reminds him of some frothy chamomile tea. Never stop being weird, Filbert.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/filbert-tea-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: ...You know, your face kinda reminds me of that sweet, frothy chamomile tea..." class="wp-image-7855" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Once I gathered up the five missing UFO parts for Gulliver, I took them back to him. He rewarded me with some chocolates. It was my third time getting chocolates from him, so I didn&amp;#8217;t really need them. But I guess it is kinda fitting to get chocolates during Christmas week, so thanks, Gulliver!&lt;em&gt; (Just give me the tribal mask next time!)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I saw a large fish shadow in the ocean. I got my fishing rod out and caught myself a big tuna.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tuna2024-150x112.jpg" alt="I caught a tuna! And I'm not talking canned!" class="wp-image-7856" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Truffles told me that Tom Nook saves bells like I wouldn&amp;#8217;t believe; she said he&amp;#8217;s neurotic! I don&amp;#8217;t think that&amp;#8217;s the right word, though. Maybe he&amp;#8217;s frugal or greedy, sure.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/truffles-neurotic-150x112.jpg" alt="Truffles: Boy, that Tom Nook... He saves bells like you WOULD NOT BELIEVE! He's neurotic!" class="wp-image-7857" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Well, Truffles, let me explain it in a way that you might relate to. Maybe he&amp;#8217;s just a &lt;em&gt;pig &lt;/em&gt;with money, and he &lt;em&gt;hogs &lt;/em&gt;all the bells for himself. He brings home the bacon and keeps it there! Oh, and you should see his &lt;em&gt;pork&lt;/em&gt;-folio! (He even owns a bunch of &lt;em&gt;Ham&lt;/em&gt;-azon stock.) 🐖&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tonight, Drift said that seeing people jogging on sandy beaches reminds him of the days when he used to bench-press killer whales!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/drift-whales-150x112.jpg" alt="Drift: Man, it takes me back! I used to bench-press killer whales, rrrrribbit!" class="wp-image-7861" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yeah, right! That&amp;#8217;s a whale of a tale. He&amp;#8217;s &lt;em&gt;drifting &lt;/em&gt;far from the truth; that&amp;#8217;s probably the least believable thing he&amp;#8217;s ever said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I later listened in on a conversation between my squirrels, Filbert and Caroline. It started out with Filbert asking Caroline if she liked him.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/caroline-wii-150x112.jpg" alt="Caroline: Of course! I like you. We are friends, after all, on my Wii." class="wp-image-7862" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But then it got &lt;strong&gt;weird&lt;/strong&gt;. Caroline called him unambitious, Filbert claimed he made a cape to become Fashion Lad, Caroline swore to defend scrunchies &lt;em&gt;to the death&lt;/em&gt;, Caroline challenged him to a fight, and Filbert said Caroline is pretty enough to get away with wearing any sort of atrocious fashion. It was wild. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/filbert-atrocious-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: Huh?! Well, you're so pretty, it doesn't matter what atrocious thing you wear." class="wp-image-7863" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At the Roost, I asked K.K. Slider to play a song for me. He performed K.K. Dixie, which isn&amp;#8217;t one of my favorites, but it was alright.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kk-122824-150x112.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Dixie!" class="wp-image-7864" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you&amp;#8217;re looking for a video to watch, even though it&amp;#8217;s not Wild World, I posted a new &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3rEhb1iECLg" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;City Folk Moments&lt;/a&gt; video today. Check it out, and have a good weekend and New Year! See you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/28/whale-of-a-tale/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-12-28T21:22:12-05:00"&gt;December 28, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-12-28T21:23:22-05:00"&gt;December 28, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
